    <string name="profile_request_deletion_confirm">This will remove local profile settings, reading history, search history, downloads, bookmarks, followed topics and local sign-in tokens on this device. This action cannot delete data from external services, but it will reset the app local account state.</string>
    <string name="profile_privacy_full_content">News Reader stores most user data locally on the device. This includes profile settings, reading history, search history, bookmarks, downloads, followed topics, muted/blocked items and app preferences. News content is loaded from NewsAPI either directly or through the backend proxy, depending on configuration. The app does not sell user data. You can clear activity data, disable personalization, remove downloads and reset local account data from this screen. Push notifications require Firebase configuration and can be disabled in settings.</string>
